name: Oracle Service Cloud
description: Add an Oracle Service Cloud Instance to connect your existing Oracle Service Cloud account to the Help Desk Hub, allowing you to manage your incidents, priorities, statuses, users, etc. across multiple Help Desk Elements. You will need your Oracle Service Cloud account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an Servicecloud account, you can create one at Service Cloud Register

configuration.name: Vendor Event Type
configuration.description: Oracle Service Cloud Vendor Event Type

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Fetch All Fields
configuration.description: Set this value if you want to retrieve all the values for an object, this fetches the ones with "Specify to Get"

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Bulk Upload Restart
configuration.description: Can Recover From Bulk Server Restart

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Objects|URL
configuration.description: An element poling Objects and URL used for event notifications from provider, if URL is not mentioned then it uses the default URL for polling for that object, format should be objectname|url

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: An application callback URL used for event notifications from Oracle Service Cloud and Cloud Elements, e.g., incidents created , etc.

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description:
Search for incidents in the help desk system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all incidents whose name contains the word 'bug', the search expression parameter will be where=name='%bug%'. Performing a search without these parameters will not return any results.

If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for incidents last modified on or after '1900-01-01', the search expression will be where=updatedTime > '1900-01-01'

parameters.name: includeDeleted
parameters.description: Specify if deleted incidents should be included in the search.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to return per page

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The one-indexed page for paginated items (e.g. '2' begins with the third item)

resources.description:
Search for comments for an incident in the help desk system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all incident comments whose name contains the word 'escalate', the search expression parameter will be where=name='%escalate%'. Performing a search without these parameters will return all the comments in paginated list.

If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the incident for the comments to be retrived

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for comments last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all comments are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: includeDeleted
parameters.description: Specify if deleted comments should be included in the search.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to return per page

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The one-indexed page for paginated items (e.g. '2' begins with the third item)

resources.description:
Find objects in the Helpdesk system, using the provided object name and CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all contacts whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name like '%data%'. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 200 records will be returned.

If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for objects that were last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all objects of the given type are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: objectName
parameters.description: The object name of the object to search, e.g., 'account'.

parameters.name: includeDeleted
parameters.description: Specify if deleted objects should be included in the search.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

resources.description:
Returns a list of objects based on a set of search parameters.  Here is an example query:  select id, name			(Fields of that Object)
from contactX			(Name of Object)
where name like '%foo%' 	(Search Expression)
or name like '%bar%;		(Search Expression continued)
order by createdDate 		(Order of Search)
limit 10 			(How Many Results to Display)
offset 0 			(Where to start in the list of objects)
In this example, I am querying a list of objects from contactX containing the fields id and name where the name contains foo or bar.  The results will be in a list of 10 organized by the date they were created, starting with the earliest.

parameters.name: q
parameters.description: The search query (i.e. select id, name from contact where name like '%foo' limit 10 offset 0
